This document outlines the steps to set up, configure, and execute the Selenium script provided in the project

1. Prerequisites
Java Development Kit (JDK):

Install JDK (version 8 or later).
Verify the installation by running java -version in your terminal.
Maven:

Install Apache Maven for dependency management.
Verify installation using mvn -version.
IDE:

Install an Integrated Development Environment (IDE) such as IntelliJ IDEA or Eclipse.
Browser Drivers:

Drivers for Chrome, Firefox, and Edge are automatically managed using WebDriverManager.
Supported Browsers:

Ensure the browsers (Chrome, Firefox, Edge) are installed and updated

Dependency Management
The project uses Maven for dependency management. Ensure the following Java, testNg and webdriverManger dependencies are included in your pom.xml file: